The paper deals with the problem of joint admission control and resource scheduling for Ultra Reliable Low Latency Communications (URLLC), which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which suggests that it could be related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper proposes heuristic algorithms for solving the problem, which could be related to systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
